HEADWORD: Peribolos
<hw>Pe*rib"o*los</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Nl., fr. Gr.
<grk>peri`bolos</grk>, fr. <grk>peri`bolos</grk>, adj., going round, fr.
<grk>periba`llein</grk> to throw round; cf. L.
<ets>peribolus</ets>.]</ety> <def>In ancient architecture, an inclosed
court, esp., one surrounding a temple.</def>⟦br⟧
